        "client_msg_id": "1C4A2648-0E46-4EF5-A1E0-C5E864225A02",
        "text": "I think sandstorm is totally worthy of its own thread. If I were to relate it back to SUA’s, I would say that the big distinctions I would make is that sandstorm is a single open source project where SUA’s aim to be more of an interoperable standard. Also sandstorm is built with a hard dependency on the Linux kernel. An SUA would be built on a web tech foundation, it couldn’t depend specifically on Linux.",
